fields.value: Women's Attitudes Questionnaire I and II (CAPS-WOMATT1 CAPS-WOMATT2 CAPS-WOMATT module)

dsDescriptionValue.value:
The Women's Attitudes Questionnaire consists of questions selected from the 'Study of North Carolina Women, 1978' conducted by Karen Gentemann of the Institute for Research in Social Science.(Codebook for this study is in the IRSS Data Library, Codebook 99-4, Cat# D-1300).

The first unit of the Women's Attitudes Questionnaire, WOMATT1, contains questions on employment of women, knowledge and attitudes towards ERA, and perceptions of women FOR and AGAINST the ERA. Due to a programming er ror in CAPS/85, those women against the ERA were not asked questions of their perceptions of women FOR and AGAINST the ERA. This error was corrected in CAPS/86.

The second unit, WOMATT2, contains questions on attitudes towards abortion, marital decision-making, and women's safety.

In CAPS/85 a merged file (WOMATTM) was created. In CAPS/87 a merged file (WOMATT) was created.

No standard scoring.

publicationCitation.value: IRSS 'Study of North Carolina Women, 1978.' See IRSS Data Library Codebook 99-4.
